Insider Activity


Individual




Blair C. Pickerell



Mr. Blair C. Pickerell is Head of Asia & Global Chief Marketing Officer at Nikko Asset Management Hong Kong Ltd.
Based in Hong Kong, he is responsible in developing and overseeing Nikko Asset Management (Nikko AM) businesses in the Asian region and implementing its branding strategy worldwide.
Mr. Pickerell has over 25 years of experience in the Asian investment management industry. Prior to joining the Nikko AM group in August 2010, he served as CEO (Asia) at Morgan Stanley Investment Management (MSIM) for three years, where he overseen MSIM's investment management offices in Hong Kong, Japan, Singapore, China, India, Australia and Korea.  Before that, he served as Chief Executive (Asia Pacific) for HSBC Asset Management, Director of The Taiwan Fund Inc. and as Chairman of JF Funds.  He also served as Managing Director of Jardine Pacific Ltd. for four years and Development Director of Mandarin Oriental Hotel Group for two years.  He first joined the investment management industry in 1985.
Mr. PIckerell received his BA degree (with honors and distinction) and MA degree from Stanford University. He also holds MBA degree from Harvard Business School.  He is fluent in Mandarin Chinese.



